FBIS4-40268 "drsov115_f_94002" FBIS-SOV-94-115 Daily Report 14 Jun 1994 National Affairs Crimea Debate Continues on Council Deputy Status Crimea Debate Continues on Council Deputy Status LD1406171994 Kiev UT-1 Television Network in Ukrainian 1600 GMT 14 Jun 94 LD1406171994 Kiev UT-1 Television Network Ukrainian BFN [Text] The Crimean parliament continued today the debate on the status of the Crimean Supreme Council deputy. Members voted against the amendment requiring them to be guided in their work not only by the law, but by their conscience. They also rejected the amendment requiring them to take an oath of loyalty to the people of Crimea. However, the majority voted to allow deputies to carry personal weapons.
